TITLE: RouterOptions Interface
DESCRIPTION: This defines the `RouterOptions` interface for configuring the Fresh router. It includes options for trailing slash behavior, ignoring files with a specific pattern, and serving fresh from a base path.
SOURCE: https://github.com/denoland/fresh/blob/main/docs/latest/concepts/server-configuration.md#2025-04-19_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export interface RouterOptions {
  /**
   *  Controls whether Fresh will append a trailing slash to the URL.
   *  @default {false}
   */
  trailingSlash?: boolean;
  /**
   *  Configures the pattern of files to ignore in islands and routes.
   *
   *  By default Fresh will ignore test files,
   *  for example files with a `.test.ts` or a `_test.ts` suffix.
   *
   *  @default {/(?:[^/]*_|[^/]*\.|)test\.(?:ts|tsx|mts|js|mjs|jsx|)\/$\/*$/}
   */
  ignoreFilePattern?: RegExp;
  /**
   * Serve fresh from a base path instead of from the root.
   *   "/foo/bar" -> http://localhost:8000/foo/bar
   * @default {undefined}
   */
  basePath?: string;
}
```

